                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4568: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-17T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 17, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 17—11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>240. Following from Gibson: Committee of experts held formal meeting this morning
                    at 11 o’clock at Treasury. Leith-Ross, Treasury representative accepted
                    chairmanship. A subcommittee is to meet this afternoon to prepare a statement as
                    to the character of various arrangements for deliveries in kind. Livesey will
                    attend. It was agreed that other Governments receiving deliveries in kind will
                    be invited to submit their views to the subcommittee.</p>
                <p>No further meeting of full committee until after the Ministers have met on
                    Monday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
